{
  "text": "At the end of the experiment, each animal was intraperitoneally injected with an excess amount of sodium pentobarbital (>80 mg/kg, Dainippon Pharmaceutical Co.) and perfused intracardially with 0.9% saline, followed by phosphate-buffered 10% formalin. The brain was removed from the skull and stored in 10% formalin for a few days. After infiltration with 30% sucrose, it was frozen, sectioned at 60-\u00b5m thickness, and stained with cresyl violet. The sections were subsequently examined under a light microscope and the locations of the cannula tips were drawn onto plates from the stereotaxic atlas of the rat brain [CITATION_1] . The distance between the targeted location and the actual location of the cannula tips was estimated by calculating the distance from the AP and DV coordinates.",
  "citation_candidates": [
